## Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React/Vite e-commerce project.

### What Was Implemented

1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart to ensure using the most up-to-date installation steps.

2. **Project Analysis**: 
   - Identified the project as a React application using Vite as the build tool
   - Confirmed pnpm as the package manager (pnpm-lock.yaml present)
   - Discovered that `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already installed in dependencies
   - Found that `@vercel/speed-insights` was already configured alongside this implementation

3. **Analytics Implementation**:
   - Added Analytics component import to `src/App.tsx`: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react"`
   - Placed `<Analytics />` component in the App component alongside the existing SpeedInsights component
   - Followed the official React/Vite framework-specific instructions from the documentation

### Modified Files

- **client/src/App.tsx**: Added Analytics import and component

### Implementation Details

Following the Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects:
- Used the `@vercel/analytics/react` import path (framework-specific)
- Placed the Analytics component at the root level of the App component
- Positioned it alongside the SpeedInsights component for consistency
- The component is self-contained and requires no props or additional configuration

### Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ Dependencies installed using pnpm
2. ✅ Build completed successfully (`pnpm run build`)
3. ⚠️ Linter has pre-existing configuration issues (ESLint v10 migration needed)
4. ⚠️ Tests have pre-existing failures unrelated to Analytics changes

### Next Steps for Deployment

According to Vercel documentation, to enable analytics:
1. Navigate to your project's Analytics dashboard on Vercel
2. Click the "Enable" button
3. Deploy the project using `vercel deploy`
4. Verify tracking by checking the browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

### Notes

- The package was already installed, indicating forward-thinking dependency management
- No additional configuration files needed for basic analytics tracking
- Analytics will automatically track page views once deployed to Vercel
- The implementation follows the same pattern as the existing SpeedInsights integration
